WEBVTT

00:04.564 --> 00:06.831
(heartbeat echoing,
heavy breathing)

00:19.779 --> 00:21.879
¶ ¶

00:25.819 --> 00:28.486
(water running)

00:40.000 --> 00:42.066
¶ ¶

00:54.047 --> 00:56.114
(heart beating faintly)

01:05.358 --> 01:07.625
Oh, thank God, you're here.

01:07.627 --> 01:08.860
Are you okay?

01:08.862 --> 01:11.662
I'm good.

01:11.664 --> 01:14.332
All of the antibiotics that
they're using aren't working.

01:14.334 --> 01:16.334
Hi, Max.

01:16.336 --> 01:18.870
(monitor beeping steadily,
air pumping)

01:18.872 --> 01:21.005
They think the pneumonia's
turning to staph.

01:21.007 --> 01:24.876
They've asked me if
I want to sign a DNR.

01:27.313 --> 01:28.846
(crying):
Please tell me

01:28.848 --> 01:30.748
that we're not there yet.

01:30.750 --> 01:32.917
I won't give up.

01:32.919 --> 01:35.319
I promise.

01:35.321 --> 01:37.121
(crying)

01:40.260 --> 01:42.560
(heart beating)

01:43.863 --> 01:47.432
Why don't you go get
a coffee or a sandwich?

01:47.434 --> 01:49.734
I'll figure it out.

02:01.181 --> 02:02.747
¶ ¶

02:02.749 --> 02:04.816
(panting)

02:28.775 --> 02:30.842
¶ ¶

02:58.104 --> 03:00.505
(monitor beeping)

03:01.975 --> 03:05.343
(rapid beeping)

03:10.650 --> 03:12.483
(monitor flatlining)

03:15.622 --> 03:16.721
(screaming)

04:26.359 --> 04:28.426
(doorbell rings)

04:29.929 --> 04:31.729
Ramona Royale-- is she in?

04:31.731 --> 04:33.164
Sir, it is 4:00 in the morning.

04:33.166 --> 04:34.765
I hear she's
a night person.

04:34.767 --> 04:36.834
Move!

04:42.909 --> 04:45.810
Ramona!

04:47.046 --> 04:48.512
Ramona Royale!

04:48.514 --> 04:50.781
What the hell?!

04:50.783 --> 04:52.250
Shall I call
the police, madam?

04:52.252 --> 04:53.517
Oh, sure, call the cops, Jeeves.

04:53.519 --> 04:54.952
I could use a snack.

04:54.954 --> 04:56.287
It's fine, Graves.

04:56.289 --> 04:57.888
I've got this.

04:57.890 --> 05:01.259
What the hell
are you doing back here?

05:01.261 --> 05:04.562
I told you already
I don't have any use for you.

05:04.564 --> 05:05.930
You were wrong about that.

05:07.600 --> 05:08.699
Who's this?

05:08.701 --> 05:09.900
(chuckles)

05:09.902 --> 05:13.037
The answer to
your prayers.

05:13.039 --> 05:15.973
You said you wanted an
inside man-- she's it.

05:15.975 --> 05:19.243
She manages
The Cortez.

05:19.245 --> 05:21.445
Hell's wrong with her?

05:21.447 --> 05:23.881
She's kind of a drunk.

05:23.883 --> 05:25.816
She'll sober up.

05:25.818 --> 05:27.451
Drunk, huh?

05:27.453 --> 05:29.620
You want to take down
The Countess?

05:29.622 --> 05:30.988
So do I.

05:30.990 --> 05:32.890
And Iris here is the key.

05:32.892 --> 05:36.594
Nobody gets closer
to The Countess than she does.

05:36.596 --> 05:38.462
You did.

05:38.464 --> 05:40.231
We both did.

05:42.435 --> 05:44.902
IRIS: You're
a movie star.

05:46.406 --> 05:48.739
Was.

05:52.979 --> 05:54.445
You're so beautiful.

05:54.447 --> 05:56.080
Yeah.

05:56.082 --> 05:57.848
Real waste, isn't it?

05:57.850 --> 05:59.183
It is a waste.

05:59.185 --> 06:01.752
Goddamn shame.

06:01.754 --> 06:03.487
She took that life
away from you.

06:03.489 --> 06:06.023
Promised you
something better,

06:06.025 --> 06:08.326
then took that away
from you, too.

06:08.328 --> 06:11.762
I know just
how that feels.

06:11.764 --> 06:14.865
You want to
make her bleed.

06:14.867 --> 06:17.835
I want that, too, 'cause
she did the same thing to me.

06:17.837 --> 06:20.771
Only, in my case,
she never even gave me a choice.

06:20.773 --> 06:24.709
Did you give
her a choice?

06:24.711 --> 06:27.044
What do you mean?

06:27.046 --> 06:28.879
Your mama.

06:28.881 --> 06:32.450
And I know that ain't
no case of the DTs.

06:32.452 --> 06:33.851
She been turned.

06:33.853 --> 06:36.787
You do that?

06:36.789 --> 06:38.456
DONOVAN: I did
what I had to do.

06:38.458 --> 06:41.892
I don't know if that's
oedipal or just mercenary.

06:41.894 --> 06:43.527
Either way...

06:43.529 --> 06:45.029
you're intrigued.

06:45.031 --> 06:48.733
You're reckless.

06:48.735 --> 06:50.401
I like that.

06:50.403 --> 06:52.069
IRIS:
We're all gonna die.

06:55.742 --> 06:56.907
She'll know.

06:56.909 --> 07:00.077
The moment she sees me,
she'll know.

07:00.079 --> 07:02.246
She never
looks at you.

07:04.817 --> 07:07.718
You're invisible.

07:07.720 --> 07:11.756
Which makes her
the perfect inside man.

07:11.758 --> 07:13.624
Right.

07:29.208 --> 07:31.909
NURSE: You know you're not
supposed to be out of bed.

07:31.911 --> 07:34.078
Doctor.

07:34.080 --> 07:36.580
Can you believe it?

07:36.582 --> 07:37.948
They thought he wouldn't
make it through the night,

07:37.950 --> 07:39.383
and here he is
begging me for snacks.

07:39.385 --> 07:42.019
Jalapeño cheddar, my fav!

07:42.021 --> 07:43.220
It's incredible.

07:43.222 --> 07:44.722
(chuckles softly)

07:44.724 --> 07:47.425
But can I see his chart?

07:49.562 --> 07:51.195
X-rays are clear.

07:51.197 --> 07:53.230
NURSE: Never seen
anything like it.

07:53.232 --> 07:55.433
He was in full
respiratory failure.

07:55.435 --> 07:57.201
It's a miracle.

07:58.871 --> 08:00.971
Yes.

08:00.973 --> 08:02.873
Yes, it is.
Does that mean

08:02.875 --> 08:03.874
we can take him home?

08:03.876 --> 08:05.443
I don't see why not.

08:05.445 --> 08:08.279
(chuckles)

08:08.281 --> 08:10.281
Doctor, I don't know
what you did,

08:10.283 --> 08:12.616
but I know you saved
my son's life.

08:12.618 --> 08:14.051
Thank you.

08:16.055 --> 08:17.822
Let's get the paperwork
ready for his discharge.

08:28.734 --> 08:30.801
(panting)

08:45.751 --> 08:48.853
Where the hell
have you been?

08:48.855 --> 08:52.022
You look like shit.

08:53.793 --> 08:55.860
What's wrong?

08:55.862 --> 08:57.495
What's wrong is
you asking me what's wrong.

08:57.497 --> 08:58.829
I just want to go to bed--
is that a problem?

08:58.831 --> 09:00.865
No, honey.

09:00.867 --> 09:03.367
Not a problem.

09:03.369 --> 09:06.670
It looks like mama

09:06.672 --> 09:08.606
needs a little
hair of the dog

09:08.608 --> 09:10.875
to help her
sleep it off.

09:14.947 --> 09:16.947
IRIS:
What is it?

09:16.949 --> 09:20.784
Liz's special
somethin' somethin'.

09:20.786 --> 09:22.853
Just drink, honey.

09:25.391 --> 09:26.957
Go ahead.

09:34.066 --> 09:37.167
Ah, that's good.

09:37.169 --> 09:39.169
Well...
It's good.

09:39.171 --> 09:40.971
it should be.

09:40.973 --> 09:42.873
It's from The Countess's

09:42.875 --> 09:44.909
secret stash.

09:44.911 --> 09:47.344
I'm drinking blood?

09:47.346 --> 09:50.648
With a drop
of triple sec.

09:52.518 --> 09:53.884
You know how this goes, honey.

09:53.886 --> 09:55.553
This little cocktail's
gonna hold you

09:55.555 --> 09:57.922
for the next couple hours,
but you're going to need

09:57.924 --> 10:00.891
to feed on fresh blood.

10:00.893 --> 10:02.493
Warm, living blood.

10:02.495 --> 10:04.762
Oh, God.
And soon.

10:04.764 --> 10:06.597
For 20 years,

10:06.599 --> 10:09.767
I looked into the eyes
of those children,

10:09.769 --> 10:14.338
and seen the pain and
the fear in their eyes.

10:14.340 --> 10:16.740
God, how am I gonna...?

10:16.742 --> 10:19.944
Oh, I can't even
say the words.

10:23.449 --> 10:25.516
Can I have some more?

10:27.687 --> 10:29.420
Sure.

10:36.796 --> 10:39.463
(laughs)
Look at you.

10:39.465 --> 10:42.967
In your moment of

10:42.969 --> 10:44.969
transplendent rebirth.

10:44.971 --> 10:47.771
How exciting to me!

10:47.773 --> 10:49.206
"How exciting"?

10:49.208 --> 10:51.775
Give me a goddamn break.

10:51.777 --> 10:54.945
This world holds nothing
for women like me.

10:54.947 --> 10:56.747
When you get to be my age,
men look right through you.

10:56.749 --> 10:57.948
(chuckles)

10:57.950 --> 10:59.583
Unless they
want something.

10:59.585 --> 11:02.786
It's not just them,
it's everyone.

11:02.788 --> 11:05.923
You're invisible,
unless you can give them a key.

11:05.925 --> 11:07.558
An extra goddamn pillow.

11:07.560 --> 11:10.260
Ask any one of those
guests upstairs

11:10.262 --> 11:12.129
who checked them in. Oh...

11:12.131 --> 11:16.066
I guarantee you, they wouldn't
remember a single detail.

11:21.440 --> 11:23.073
It's ironic.

11:23.075 --> 11:24.608
Isn't it?

11:24.610 --> 11:28.846
I'm damned to eternity
in this body.

11:28.848 --> 11:31.682
With this life.

11:31.684 --> 11:35.853
This... dark,
meaningless little soul.

11:35.855 --> 11:38.322
Right when it's
never been worse.

11:41.961 --> 11:44.728
Hmm.

11:47.366 --> 11:50.267
Yeah, I guess it's just me

11:50.269 --> 11:54.271
and the one-armed bandit
down at Morongo's,

11:54.273 --> 11:57.608
every Saturday night
till the end of time.

11:57.610 --> 11:59.209
You never know when you're gonna
get lucky, honey.

12:01.280 --> 12:05.282
You might try a little
violet eye shadow.

12:05.284 --> 12:08.318
It works for me every time.

12:08.320 --> 12:10.387
¶ ¶

12:13.492 --> 12:15.559
(bus approaching outside)

12:20.700 --> 12:22.700
(brakes squeak)

12:22.702 --> 12:24.768
(horn honks)

13:05.377 --> 13:06.744
Where were you?

13:06.746 --> 13:08.278
You didn't
answer my texts.

13:08.280 --> 13:09.747
I almost died.

13:09.749 --> 13:11.381
No way.
WOMAN: Max.

13:11.383 --> 13:14.384
I thought the letter that
we sent home was very clear.

13:14.386 --> 13:15.886
No weapons allowed in school.

13:15.888 --> 13:17.621
It's plastic.
It's a sword,

13:17.623 --> 13:19.356
no matter what it's made of.
Come on.

13:22.762 --> 13:25.195
Thank you.

13:25.197 --> 13:26.964
Come help with decorations.

13:26.966 --> 13:28.766
Stupid rules.

13:28.768 --> 13:31.735
Pritchard took
my witch's wand.

13:31.737 --> 13:34.304
I've got a backup.

13:35.875 --> 13:37.975
I missed you.

13:45.551 --> 13:47.551
So tell the truth.

13:47.553 --> 13:49.553
You weren't
really gonna die.

13:49.555 --> 13:50.788
I was in the hospital.

13:50.790 --> 13:51.989
Measles.

13:51.991 --> 13:53.557
I had red spots

13:53.559 --> 13:55.392
all over.

13:55.394 --> 13:56.927
Ew.

13:56.929 --> 13:59.062
Are you contagious?

14:00.099 --> 14:02.966
I'm so much better now.

14:09.175 --> 14:10.808
Ow!

14:10.810 --> 14:12.709
Did you just bite me?

14:14.847 --> 14:16.580
There.

14:17.917 --> 14:19.917
We're even.

14:19.919 --> 14:22.853
Now you can
taste my blood.

14:25.925 --> 14:27.691
Okay, guys,
I know it's Halloween,

14:27.693 --> 14:29.359
and we're all excited
about the party,

14:29.361 --> 14:31.795
but that does not mean
there won't be class work today.

14:31.797 --> 14:35.566
So open your books to chapter
three, "Synonyms and Antonyms."

14:37.203 --> 14:39.169
Where are Max and Madeline?

14:39.171 --> 14:41.071
(students murmuring, giggling)

14:44.810 --> 14:46.043
PRITCHARD:
What happened?

14:46.045 --> 14:48.245
(crying):
I'm itchy all over.

14:49.782 --> 14:51.682
Oh, you are burning up.

14:53.786 --> 14:55.919
(screams)

14:57.456 --> 14:58.956
(groans)

14:58.958 --> 15:00.490
What are you doing?!
Drink it.

15:00.492 --> 15:02.659
Drink it, Maddie.

15:02.661 --> 15:04.561
You're gonna
be stronger

15:04.563 --> 15:06.730
and feel better
than you've ever felt.

15:16.876 --> 15:18.876
Jimmy?

15:18.878 --> 15:20.510
I don't feel good.

15:20.512 --> 15:21.745
Let's get you
to the nurse.

15:21.747 --> 15:23.380
Where's Mrs. Pritchard?

15:27.987 --> 15:29.686
(students groaning, coughing)

15:29.688 --> 15:31.755
What?

15:34.093 --> 15:35.826
Mrs. Pritchard!

15:39.765 --> 15:41.765
It's not my fault.

15:41.767 --> 15:43.767
(panting)

15:45.704 --> 15:47.004
Oh, my...

15:48.440 --> 15:50.774
(grunting)

15:56.916 --> 15:59.516
Drink. It'll make you
feel awesome.

16:07.126 --> 16:08.025
(groaning)

16:15.801 --> 16:18.835
(screaming)
No!

16:20.773 --> 16:22.706
(screaming)

16:41.593 --> 16:44.828
You know, Patty, your costume is
really culturally insensitive.

16:44.830 --> 16:47.130
You have that dot
on your forehead.

16:47.132 --> 16:48.632
I'm Hindu.

16:48.634 --> 16:50.634
I love Halloween.

16:50.636 --> 16:53.637
I like the candy,
I like the costumes,

16:53.639 --> 16:55.973
and I love being scared.

16:55.975 --> 16:57.240
(screams)

16:57.242 --> 16:58.575
Shit.

17:01.847 --> 17:04.147
(gagging)

17:04.149 --> 17:05.916
I'm gonna move your
hand now, okay?

17:05.918 --> 17:08.285
Jill, come help me now!
He's been attacked!

17:08.287 --> 17:09.920
Patty, put the
school in lockdown!

17:11.690 --> 17:13.991
Lockdown, lockdown.

17:13.993 --> 17:16.460
This is not a drill.
Lockdown, lockdown.

17:16.462 --> 17:18.528
(alarm blaring)

17:22.434 --> 17:24.701
(sirens wailing)

17:24.703 --> 17:26.169
(helicopter flying overhead)

17:32.878 --> 17:34.011
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

17:55.868 --> 17:57.334
I want that perimeter secure.

17:57.336 --> 17:59.403
No one goes in or out.

17:59.405 --> 18:01.905
(crowd murmuring)

18:18.924 --> 18:20.190
Don't be afraid.

18:20.192 --> 18:22.492
You're safe now.

18:38.844 --> 18:40.911
¶ ¶

18:55.360 --> 18:57.427
MAN:
Madeline!

18:59.364 --> 19:01.932
Daddy! Daddy.

19:01.934 --> 19:04.234
Sir, I'm sorry, we have
an ongoing situation.

19:04.236 --> 19:05.802
I need to ask your daughter
some questions.

19:05.804 --> 19:07.537
Okay.

19:07.539 --> 19:09.773
Madeline, I know you've
been through a lot,

19:09.775 --> 19:11.308
but you're safe.

19:11.310 --> 19:14.277
No one's gonna hurt
you anymore, okay?

19:14.279 --> 19:16.279
Can you tell me what happened
inside the school?

19:16.281 --> 19:18.815
How many people
attacked you?

19:18.817 --> 19:21.084
Th-There was just one man.

19:21.086 --> 19:23.086
Dressed in black.

19:23.088 --> 19:26.089
He had a mask over his face.

19:26.091 --> 19:28.158
And he cut Mrs.
Pritchard with a knife.

19:31.597 --> 19:35.499
Um, and he was a big guy, and he
had a mask on his face, and...

19:35.501 --> 19:36.900
Son.

19:36.902 --> 19:38.168
How are you feeling?

19:38.170 --> 19:41.671
Are you up to answering
some questions?

19:41.673 --> 19:42.973
Yes, sir.

19:42.975 --> 19:45.308
I know exactly what happened.

19:58.357 --> 20:00.090
You want to explain to me
what happened last night?

20:00.092 --> 20:02.792
Uh, they-they must have
drugged me.

20:02.794 --> 20:04.261
Yeah.

20:04.263 --> 20:06.029
Let's talk about the suspects.

20:06.031 --> 20:07.030
John Wayne Gacy,

20:07.032 --> 20:08.598
Jeffrey Dahmer,

20:08.600 --> 20:10.600
Richard Ramirez,
Aileen Wuornos?

20:10.602 --> 20:12.302
Not saying it was them.

20:12.304 --> 20:13.670
Of course it wasn't.

20:13.672 --> 20:15.272
That's who they
claimed to be.

20:15.274 --> 20:16.806
It's Halloween, Detective.
Did it ever occur to you

20:16.808 --> 20:18.041
that maybe
they might...

20:18.043 --> 20:19.309
Yeah, of course
it occurred to me!

20:19.311 --> 20:22.479
That's not what this is.

20:22.481 --> 20:24.948
Okay, so what is it?

20:28.520 --> 20:30.320
It's, uh...

20:30.322 --> 20:32.455
(mumbles)

20:32.457 --> 20:34.624
Must be some kind of...

20:34.626 --> 20:36.826
copycat blood cult.

20:36.828 --> 20:38.795
<i> I don't know,</i>
<i> you call it what you want to.</i>

20:38.797 --> 20:42.465
It was people who are recreating
or are continuing

20:42.467 --> 20:45.869
the crimes committed by
notorious killers from the past.

20:45.871 --> 20:48.004
(man screams)
March-- there was a guy.

20:48.006 --> 20:50.807
One guy called himself March,
James Patrick March.

20:50.809 --> 20:52.842
You just check out the
history of the hotel.

20:52.844 --> 20:54.644
That's the name of
the guy who built it.

20:54.646 --> 20:56.713
And you had dinner with him.

20:58.483 --> 21:01.851
I was in a room with a guy
who claimed to be him,

21:01.853 --> 21:03.853
a guy who I think is responsible

21:03.855 --> 21:06.756
for the five dead bodies
on the wall in my office!

21:06.758 --> 21:09.359
You think he's
The Ten Commandment Killer?

21:09.361 --> 21:10.961
I do.

21:12.364 --> 21:13.897
I do.

21:13.899 --> 21:17.167
Lieutenant, we need
to get a-a warrant,

21:17.169 --> 21:18.668
cadaver dogs, forensics team.

21:18.670 --> 21:19.936
We need to rip
those walls apart,

21:19.938 --> 21:21.504
down to the studs
if you have to,

21:21.506 --> 21:23.173
'cause the answers are in there!

21:23.175 --> 21:25.342
I'd stake my reputation on it.

21:25.344 --> 21:26.910
You're gonna have to ante up
more than that

21:26.912 --> 21:28.245
because your reputation's shit.

21:28.247 --> 21:29.879
(sighs)

21:29.881 --> 21:32.782
Let's be honest,
it has been for a while.

21:32.784 --> 21:34.584
What's that supposed to mean?

21:34.586 --> 21:36.386
It means I probably should
never have signed off

21:36.388 --> 21:38.188
on that marginal psych
evaluation you received

21:38.190 --> 21:40.790
five years ago
after your breakdown.

21:44.563 --> 21:47.364
That was different.

21:47.366 --> 21:49.366
Our son had been taken.

21:49.368 --> 21:51.901
I was under a lot of stress.

21:51.903 --> 21:53.470
This job is stress, John.

21:53.472 --> 21:55.905
(sighs)

21:55.907 --> 21:57.974
I'm sorry.

21:57.976 --> 22:00.143
I'm gonna have to do what's
right for the department.

22:01.380 --> 22:03.780
You're firing me.

22:03.782 --> 22:06.516
Your pension will be safe.

22:17.262 --> 22:20.597
Nothing is safe.

22:20.599 --> 22:21.898
Nothing.

22:25.337 --> 22:27.337
¶ ¶

22:42.587 --> 22:44.587
(bell dings)

22:44.589 --> 22:46.656
(clears throat)

22:51.863 --> 22:53.863
How can I help you?

22:53.865 --> 22:55.865
We're wondering if
you had any special rates

22:55.867 --> 22:58.268
for, like, influencers.

23:01.306 --> 23:03.306
I beg your pardon?

23:03.308 --> 23:08.111
Uh, well, um, I used to shoot
for<i> Entrez-Vous Magazine,</i>

23:08.113 --> 23:11.481
and I heard that
Will Drake took over,

23:11.483 --> 23:14.084
and he's liked a shit-ton
of my Instagram pics.

23:16.021 --> 23:19.022
We would like a room.

23:19.024 --> 23:19.556
And a discount.

